WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.570 --> 00:00:03.480
We'll begin our foray into networking by reviewing the history of

00:00:03.480 --> 00:00:07.540
the internet and its design principles. Networking today is an eclectic mix

00:00:07.540 --> 00:00:11.060
of theory and practice in large part because the early internet

00:00:11.060 --> 00:00:15.610
architects set out with clear goals and allowed flexibility in achieving them.

00:00:15.610 --> 00:00:17.100
&gt;&gt; With all that flexibility, does that

00:00:17.100 --> 00:00:19.140
mean we'll see the rollout of IPv6 soon?

00:00:19.140 --> 00:00:20.350
&gt;&gt; Only in your dreams.

